CONTENT NOTES

This repository contains:

1. ORIGINAL WORK (covered by MIT License above):
   - .ztprog backing track format and schema
   - .ztex exercise definition format and schema
   - .ztplay playlist format and schema
   - Python source code (src/)
   - All backing track definitions and exercise metadata

2. PUBLIC DOMAIN REFERENCES:
   The following traditional/folk melodies referenced in exercises are in the
   public domain:
   - Amazing Grace (1779)
   - Old Joe Clark (traditional Appalachian)
   - Muleskinner Blues (traditional)
   - Wildwood Flower (1860)
   - Blackberry Blossom (traditional)

3. EDUCATIONAL MUSIC THEORY CONCEPTS:
   References to standard music theory concepts (enclosures, ii-V-I progressions,
   Barry Harris method, bebop vocabulary, etc.) are used for educational purposes.
   These are teachable concepts and not proprietary intellectual property.

4. MIDI FILES:
   MIDI files in this repository are original compositions/arrangements created
   for educational practice purposes.
